# Form components

Use the project‚Äôs custom form components for all form fields. They already provide labels, error display, and consistent styling via `InputWrapper`.

## Do

- **RegularInput** ‚Äì text/email/number etc. Pass `label="Field label"` (and optional `required`, `errors`, `placeholder`).
- **RegularSelect** ‚Äì dropdowns. Pass `label="Field label"`, `value`, `onSelectChange`, `options` (array of `{ value, text }` or `SelectOption`), and `placeholder`. Do not use raw `Select`/`SelectTrigger`/`SelectContent`/`SelectItem` for form fields.
- **RegularTextarea** ‚Äì multi-line text. Pass `label="Field label"` (and optional `required`, `errors`, `rows`).

Use the components‚Äô `label` prop for the visible label. Do not add a separate `<label>` element for the same field.

```tsx
// ‚úÖ GOOD ‚Äì single component with label prop
<RegularInput
  label="Your Name (Optional)"
  placeholder="Enter your name"
  value={name}
  onChange={e => setName(e.target.value)}
/>
<RegularSelect
  label="Category"
  value={category}
  onSelectChange={setCategory}
  placeholder="Select category"
  options={CATEGORY_OPTIONS}
/>
<RegularTextarea
  label="Your Testimony"
  placeholder="Share your story..."
  value={content}
  onChange={e => setContent(e.target.value)}
  required
/>
```

## Don‚Äôt

- Do not wrap these components in a separate `<label>` or `<div>` just to show a label; use the component‚Äôs `label` prop.
- Do not use the raw UI `Select`, `SelectTrigger`, `SelectContent`, `SelectItem` for standard form dropdowns; use **RegularSelect** with an `options` array (e.g. `{ value: string, text: string }[]`).
- Do not use raw `Input` or `Textarea` from `@/components/ui/*` when a labeled field is needed; use **RegularInput** or **RegularTextarea** with the `label` prop.

```tsx
// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äì redundant label + raw Select
<label htmlFor="category" className="text-sm font-medium">Category</label>
<Select value={category} onValueChange={setCategory}>
  <SelectTrigger><SelectValue placeholder="Select" /></SelectTrigger>
  <SelectContent>
    <SelectItem value="a">A</SelectItem>
  </SelectContent>
</Select>

// ‚ùå BAD ‚Äì separate label when component has label prop
<label htmlFor="name">Your Name</label>
<RegularInput id="name" label="" placeholder="..." value={name} onChange={...} />
```

## Exceptions

- **Group labels**: A single heading/label for a group of inputs (e.g. ‚ÄúPoll Options‚Äù) is fine; use the components‚Äô `label` prop for each individual field, or `label=""` for repeated fields in the group.
- **Checkboxes / custom controls**: Native `<input type="checkbox">` with a `<label>` is acceptable when no custom checkbox component exists.
- **Low-level UI**: Using raw `Select`/`Input`/`Textarea` inside shared components (e.g. `RegularSelect`, `PhoneInput`) is fine.
